{"lemma":"فَضْلَةٌ","slug":"فَضْلَةٌ","root":"ف.ض.ل","root_slug":"ف-ض-ل","root_link":"/words/roots/ف-ض-ل","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":false},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":1,"pos_tags":["noun"],"has_etymology":true,"sense_count":3},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n34082"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D9%81%D9%8E%D8%B6%D9%92%D9%84%D9%8E%D8%A9%D9%8C"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"noun","gloss":"what remains, residue, remainder"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"feces"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"a word that is used in addition to words normally used"}]},"etymology":{"source":"wiktextract","text":"Instance noun from فَضَلَ (faḍala, “to be left over”)."},"ipa":["/fadˤ.la/"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n34082","headword_ar":"فَضْلَةٌ","root":"fDl","body":[{"kind":"text","text":": see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"faDolN","text_ar":"فَضْلٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", former half, in two places. ―         -b2-  [Hence, as used by grammarians,]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A dispensable member of a proposition;"},{"kind":"text","text":"such as the objective complement of a verb, when the suppression thereof is not detrimental [to the meaning];"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"contr. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EumodapN","text_ar":"عُمْدَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (I'Ak, p. 143) [The pl. is"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"faDalaAtN","text_ar":"فَضَلَاتٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":".] ―         -b3-  And The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"clothes that are used for sleeping"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"therein"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: (K, TA:) [so called] because they are an addition over and above the clothes that are used on various [other] occasions. (TA.) ―         -b4-  And"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Wine;"},{"kind":"text","text":"and so ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fiDaAlN","text_ar":"فِضَالٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"[which see also in what here follows]: (O, K:)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlfaDolapu","text_ar":"الفَضْلَةُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is mentioned by A'Obeyd as"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a name for wine:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(O:) or it signifies, accord. to AHn,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the wine that alters"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"has become altered"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in colour after oldness;"},{"kind":"text","text":"and ISd says that it is so called because the choice, or best, or most excellent, part thereof [for"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"lA^n~","text_ar":"لانّ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HmymhA","text_ar":"حميمها"},{"kind":"text","text":"in my original (an obvious mistranscription) I read"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"liA^an~a SamiymahaA","text_ar":"لِاَنَّ صَمِيمَهَا"},{"kind":"text","text":"] is what remains: (TA:) the pl. is"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"faDalaAtN","text_ar":"فَضَلَاتٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fiDaAlN","text_ar":"فِضَالٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[the latter word mentioned above as a syn. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"faDolapN","text_ar":"فَضْلَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (K.)"}],"source_refs":["K","TA","O"]}]},"classical_definitions":null}